text: When you are in a relationship, things can change at any time. In general, a relationship can follow one of four paths. You can live together indefinitely; you can break up indefinitely; you can break up but remain connected in some way; and you can break up, make up, and then break up again. The final option, which involves repeatedly ending and renewing a relationship, is referred to as on and off relationships or relationship cycling. It is usually very harmful not only to the relationship but also to both parties.
